keywords:
  - water quality
  - machine learning
  - binary classification
  - Estonia
  - open data
  - environmental monitoring
  - risk assessment
abstract: >-
  Probabilistic risk estimator for water quality compliance in Estonia.
  Classifies whether water samples violate health norms based on 15
  chemical and biological parameters using Logistic Regression, Random
  Forest, Gradient Boosting, and LightGBM models. Built on 69,536
  samples from Terviseamet open data (2021-2026). Includes a public
  citizen service at h2oatlas.ee with interactive map visualization.
